                "message": "Fix flow control issue with walrus+exceptions (#7514)\n\nFixes #7462\n\nIf an assignment node is in an exception block, then `mark_assignment`\ncan change `self.flow.block`. This means that `self.flow.block` at the\nend of evaluation an `if` condition might be different to\n`self.flow.block` at the start. Therefore, we continue from the state at\nthe end.\n\nAlso fix the equivalent thing in match-case guard blocks.\n\nAlso add a small print function just because it was useful for debugging\nthis.",
